Here are both approaches for MAUI Shell navigation with `IQueryAttributable`:

**1. Register your route:**
```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (both approaches):**
```csharp
// Approach A – pass primitive (string ID)
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B – pass full object
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", navParams);
}
```

**3. Receive data in the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**
```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A – primitive arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            ProductId = idObj.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B – complex object passed via dictionary overload
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var prodObj) && prodObj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page:**
```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Navigation call** | `GoToAsync($"...?key={val}")` | `GoToAsync("...", Dictionary)` |
| **Survives deep-link / URL** | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| **Passes complex data** | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| **Type in `ApplyQueryAttributes`** | `string` | Original object type |

Use **string params** for bookmarkable/deep-linkable navigation; use **object params** when you already have the data in memory and want to avoid a redundant lookup.
